  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "QUfMIxyYiSH+ChJv0iyc8wM2qe4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Cross-user sharing via Swarm ACT (Access Control Trie)\n\n### Key derivation\n\n```\nsession_key = SHA-256(\n  ECDH(publisher_privkey x grantee_pubkey)\n  || salt\n)\n```\n\nOnly the publisher's Bee node holds `publisher_privkey`, so a third party who knows both public addresses still cannot derive the key (discrete-log problem). Grantees derive the same `session_key` independently using their own private key.\n\n### Upload / download API shape\n\n```\nUpload:   uploadFile({ act: true, actHistoryAddress, skipEncryption })\nDownload: downloadFile({ actPublisher, actHistoryAddress, skipDecryption })\n```\n\n`skipEncryption`/`skipDecryption` on the client side means **Bee** handles crypto (it knows the private key), not the browser. The client supplies `actHistoryAddress` to identify which grantee set applies.\n\n### Grantee management\n\n- `createGrantees([...pubkeys])` \u2014 initial grantee set plus history address.\n- `patchGrantees(...)` \u2014 add/remove grantees over time.\n\nUsed for three distinct features:\n\n1. **Document sharing** \u2014 a drive bundle shared to another user.\n2. **Chat history feeds** \u2014 per-conversation ACT feeds.\n3. **Raw chat attachments** \u2014 files attached to messages.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
    }
  },
